{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:15:59.282789+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 570, "prompt_tokens": 8980, "total_tokens": 9550, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8768, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002138304, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 5.42304e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0001596}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780874151-eGitu2bGS2dKxf91Ap3Z", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea45f-078a-77e3-ba08-2325ddbfaf4c-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the detailed report — your analysis is spot on.\n\n**Triage summary: the library (token bucket in `bucket.lua`) is working correctly; the issue is with the example's documentation/copy, not with the core algorithm.**\n\nHere's what's happening:\n\n1. **The library is correct.** `bucket.lua` implements a standard token-bucket algorithm: it refills tokens at `refill_per_sec` based on elapsed wall-clock time, then tries to consume `cost` tokens. This is textbook token-bucket behavior.\n\n2. **The example is misleading.** `examples/flask_app.py` uses:\n   ```python\n   capacity=10\n   refill_per_sec=10 / 60  # ~0.167 tokens/sec\n   ```\n   The docstring says *\"rate-limit to 10 requests per minute per IP\"* — but token bucket semantics allow an initial burst of `capacity=10` tokens **plus** continuous refill. Over 60 seconds at `10/60` tokens/sec, you get ~10 more refilled tokens, yielding roughly **20 requests** in the first minute. This is correct token-bucket behavior, not a bug in the algorithm.\n\n3. **The README is also slightly misleading.** The API section shows `refill_per_sec=1.0` without clarifying how `capacity` and `refill_per_sec` interact to define the effective rate. The example quickstart says \"repeat until rate limited\" without setting expectations about burst vs. sustained rate.\n\n**Suggested fixes (example, not library changes):**\n\n- Update the `flask_app.py` docstring to clarify burst behavior, e.g.: *\"Allows an initial burst of 10 requests, then sustains ~10 requests/minute.\"*\n- Optionally, add a comment in the example explaining that token bucket = burst capacity + sustained refill.\n- The README could benefit from a brief \"Understanding the parameters\" section explaining how `capacity` (burst) and `refill_per_sec` (sustained rate) compose.\n\n**No code change to `bucket.lua` or `limiter.py` is needed** — the library implements token bucket correctly and atomically. This is purely a documentation/example clarification.\n\n@BruceKZ — does that match your understanding? Happy to draft the doc fixes if so."}, "id": "call_806d124ebf49481089457ef5", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8980, "output_tokens": 570, "total_tokens": 9550, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8768}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
