{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:16:07.108029+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The tool doesn't have permission to write comments or labels on this repo, so I can't take action directly. Here's my triage and recommended action:\n\n---\n\n## Triage: Issue #1 — \"Rate limit allows ~2x configured rate when bursting\"\n\n**Verdict: The reporter is correct. This is an example/documentation issue, not a library bug.**\n\n### Evidence from the code\n\n**`bucket.lua`** (the core algorithm) implements a textbook token-bucket:\n- On each call, it calculates elapsed time, refills tokens at `refill_per_sec * elapsed`, caps at `capacity`, then subtracts `cost`.\n- This is correct and atomic (runs as a single Redis `EVALSHA`).\n\n**`examples/flask_app.py`** configures:\n```python\ncapacity=10\nrefill_per_sec=10 / 60  # ≈ 0.167 tokens/sec\n```\nwith the docstring: *\"rate-limit a Flask endpoint to 10 requests per minute per IP.\"*\n\n### Why you see ~20 requests in the first 60s\n\nThe token bucket starts full at 10 tokens (the burst). Over 60 seconds, it refills 10 more tokens at the configured rate. Total = **10 (burst) + 10 (refill) = ~20 requests** in the first minute. This is correct token-bucket semantics — the reporter's analysis is spot on.\n\nThe example's docstring is misleading because it implies a hard 10/min cap, but `capacity` is the burst size, and the sustained rate is governed by `refill_per_sec`.\n\n### Recommended action\n\n1. **Label:** `documentation` (not a bug)\n2. **Comment** explaining the above — the library works correctly; the example's docstring should clarify burst vs. sustained behavior.\n3. **Do not close** until the example is updated, since the mislabeling could confuse other users.\n\n### Suggested docstring fix for `flask_app.py`:\n```python\n\"\"\"Demo: rate-limit a Flask endpoint.\n\nBucket capacity=10 allows an initial burst of 10 requests.\nRefill rate: 10 tokens/minute (~0.167/sec) for sustained traffic.\nTotal in first minute: up to ~20 (10 burst + 10 refilled).\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n**I wasn't able to post the comment or apply labels** due to token permission limitations (403). If you'd like me to try a different approach or if you can grant write access, I can retry.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 578, "prompt_tokens": 9599, "total_tokens": 10177, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 25, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8960, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000276388, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000114548, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00016184}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780874159-55wIvFg6qNlQh3Uvp8Ai", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea45f-25c0-7ae1-bc49-cb1499f6bca5-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9599, "output_tokens": 578, "total_tokens": 10177, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8960}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 25}}}}]}}}
